		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">thefox wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Does the label file tell you what segment each label is in? If so, translate segments to MEMORY areas to banks.</div><br />It doesn't. It's very basic file specifically for use with VICE, but the linker source should be pretty easy to modify to spit out the segment info too.</div>
<br />
<br />It you use the --dbgfile option on the linker, it will spit out some extra information and the segments are listed at the begining with some address.  Since I didn't test it with a multi-bank program yet, I don't know how useful this information will be.

		

